sentences: Hobart Earle (born December 20, 1960) is a Venezuelan-born conductor of American descent and People's Artist of Ukraine recipient.

He has recorded works by such composers as Mykola Kolessa, Myroslav Skoryk, Yevhen Stankovych and Reinhold Gliere that were not previously recorded.

Earle's performance of Tchaikovsky's 5th symphony, recorded live in concert by Austrian broadcaster ORF in Vienna's Musikverein, was awarded Best Classical Album in California in 2002, and his live recording of Myroslav Skoryk's 75th birthday concerts was selected for the "Chairman's Choice 2014 – Klaus Heymann's Favorite Naxos Releases."
